  "name": "RPlog_Guest_of_the_Empire_part_1",
  "title": "Guest of the Empire, Part I",
  "summary": "Following a space battle in which her X-wing was destroyed by the Broadsword, the badly burned New Republic Chyleni pilot Kyrin Sh'vani is recovered by a stormtrooper team and brought aboard the Imperial Star Destroyer. Captain Caiton, the doctor-turned-commander, leads the medical triage with clinical fascination at the rare alien physiology, while Marshal Krieg secures the area and keeps the ship combat-ready, and Commissar Lanil Jast and the formidable 501st Legion General Petra Doom arrive to assess the prisoner's value. Petra orders Kyrin stabilized and held until ISB Commissar Fleming can interrogate her. Once healed, Kyrin is examined again as Fleming arrives, openly disgusted by her non-human form, and the two clinically catalogue her wings and tail before demanding her assignment and intelligence on the Republic's blockade-running over Coruscant. When she refuses, Fleming has her wings strapped to surgical trays and marches her humiliatingly through the ship to a detention cell, where she is bound, her eyes clamped open, and forced to watch a looping recording of the Jedi Brandis Finian being tortured. Kyrin endures it with serene dignity, retreating into memories of better times.",
